  "response": "For most MSI laptops, you can typically replace both the hard disk and RAM. However, the specific process and accessibility can vary depending on the exact model. Here are some general guidelines:\n\n1. RAM:\n- Most MSI laptops have easily accessible RAM slots\n- Often, you can upgrade RAM by removing a bottom panel\n- Check your laptop's manual or specifications to confirm maximum RAM capacity and compatible types\n\n2. Hard Disk:\n- Many MSI laptops allow hard drive replacement\n- You can typically replace:\n  - Traditional HDD (Hard Disk Drive)\n  - SSD (Solid State Drive)\n- Some newer models might have different configurations\n\nRecommended steps:\n1. Check your specific laptop model's manual\n2. Verify compatibility of new RAM/storage\n3. Ensure you have the right tools\n4. Consider professional installation if you're not comfortable\n5. Back up your data before replacement\n\nIf you provide your exact MSI laptop model, I can give you more precise information about replacement procedures.\n\nWould you like me to help you find specific details for your laptop?",
